All density functional theory (DFT) calculations are performed using Gaussian 98 program package [33]. First, a selected triangular GQD with hydrogen passivated edges, with zigzag edge size n
                     =6, which is consisted of 61 carbon atoms and 21 hydrogen atoms, is considered as a starting point for the design of N/B doped triangular GQDs, allowed to fully relax during the UB3LYP/6-31G* optimization process. In this structure the hexagonal lattice of graphene contained two sets of sublattices, denoted as A and B (Fig. 1
                     ).
